subtitleNullable: Unlocking the Spirits of Iowa: sales of individual products at the store level.
descriptionNullable:
This dataset contains the spirits purchase information of Iowa Class “E” liquor licensees by product and date of purchase from January 1, 2022 to December 31, 2022. The dataset can be used to analyze total spirits sales in Iowa of individual products at the store level.

Class E liquor license, for grocery stores, liquor stores, convenience stores, etc., allows commercial establishments to sell liquor for off-premises consumption in original unopened containers.

The whole data set is available on [data.iowa.gov](https://data.iowa.gov/). Use the explore tab to filter the data that you need for the analysis at their website.

This dataset was processed before being uploaded at Kaggle. 

Using the [View Data](https://data.iowa.gov/Sales-Distribution/Iowa-Liquor-Sales/m3tr-qhgy/explore) tab, we used these filters to retrieve the data for analysis:  
-> Date between 2022 Jan 01 12:00:00 AM and 2021 Dec 31 11:59:59 PM 

-> Sales (Dollars) > 0 

-> Category name is NOT NULL. 

With those filters, we got 2,563,482 unique sales.
